data.enText: an object that fits into the top of a bottle to close it

data.text: lid ♦ top ♦ cork ♦ cap ♦ plug ♦ stopper

data.chText: 以上各词均指容器的盖、盖子。
data.enText: These are all words for a cover for a container.
a cover over a container that can be removed or opened by turning or lifting it

data.chText: 盖子严丝合缝的广口瓶
data.enText: a jar with a tight-fitting lid
a thing that you put over the end of sth such as a pen or bottle in order to close it

data.chText: 指尤用于酒瓶的软木塞、塑料瓶塞
data.enText: a small round object made of cork or plastic that is used for closing bottles, especially wine bottles

data.chText: （常构成复合词）指钢笔、照相机镜头等的盖、帽
data.enText: (often in compounds) a top for a pen or a protective cover for sth such as the lens of a camera

data.chText: 指栓塞、堵塞物、水池的塞子：
data.enText: a round piece of material that you put into a hole in order to block it; a flat round rubber or plastic thing that you put into the hole of a sink in order to stop the water from flowing out

data.chText: 在美国英语中，plug亦用以指瓶塞：
data.enText: In American English, the word plug is also used to mean a stopper.
a bottle with a glass plug
an object that fits into the top of a bottle to close it
a bottle with a glass stopper
to put on/screw on/take off/unscrew the lid/top/cap

tr: blockage consisting of an object designed to fill a hole tightly
(bridge) a playing card with a value sufficiently high to insure taking a trick in a particular suit
example: if my partner has a spade stopper I can bid no trump

tr: a remark to which there is no polite conversational reply
an act so striking or impressive that the show must be delayed until the audience quiets down
close or secure with or as if with a stopper
example: The mothers stoppered their babies' mouths with pacifiers

value.def: A stopper is a piece of glass, plastic, or cork that fits into the top of a bottle or jar to close it.

example.ex: ...a bottle of colourless liquid sealed with a cork stopper.
example.tran: 用软木塞封口的一瓶无色液体
